{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778620882,"nonce":"3i//TW1DFlJI/vMNFeNxY2G7Yxw=","title":"Forward velocity profiles used absolute-time aggregation instead of go-cue alignment","message":"## Problem\nSome recent forward-velocity profile figures were interpreted as go-cue-aligned trial summaries, but the known analysis code for the `f47abb1` and `3702f54` figures did not actually align trials to each trial's go cue before averaging. It averaged velocity profiles in absolute trial time, then drew a vertical line at the mean go-cue index.\n\nThis can make movement onset appear earlier than it is in true go-aligned coordinates, because trials with early go cues contribute post-go movement before the mean-go vertical line. It also makes the plotted error bands easy to misread: in the affected figures the band is across replicate-mean traces after trial averaging, not trial-level variability across early/late go-cue trials.\n\n## Evidence\nKnown implementation pattern in the affected scripts:\n\n- `go_idx = trial_specs.timeline.epoch_bounds[:, 2]` is computed.\n- The plot uses `t = np.arange(n_steps) * dt`, i.e. absolute trial time.\n- It then computes `v_mean_over_trials = v_fwd.mean(axis=1)`, averaging trials before any go-cue alignment.\n- It draws `fig.add_vline(x=float(mean_go) * dt, ...)`, where `mean_go = int(go_idx.mean())`.\n- The figure spec for `results/3702f54/figures/forward_velocity_profiles/spec.json` records `mean_over_trials` and `mean_sd_across_replicates`, with no trial-to-go alignment transform.\n\nConcrete diagnostic on `full_trial_pl__prego_1` from `3702f54`:\n\n- Evaluated go indices were `[23, 23, 19, 25, 11, 23, 14, 25]`.\n- Old absolute-time mean, plotted relative to the mean-go line, crossed `0.01 m/s` at about `+20 ms`.\n- A corrected go-aligned re-evaluation crossed `0.01 m/s` at about `+80 ms`.\n- Individual replicate-trial onsets at the same threshold were mostly `70-90 ms` after the true aligned go cue.\n\nSo the old figure can hide an approximately 5-8 step reaction delay by smearing early-go trials into the pre-/near-go region of a mean-go plot.\n\n## Known affected surfaces\nLikely or known affected:\n\n- `scripts/analyse_pregomatrix.py` velocity-profile figure generation for the `3702f54` pre-go motor-mask matrix.\n- `results/3702f54/figures/forward_velocity_profiles/figure.html` and `spec.json`.\n- The second and seventh subplots of that figure were explicitly inspected: `lit__full_nojerk` and `full_trial_pl__prego_1`.\n- All other subplots in that same `3702f54` forward-velocity figure likely share the same aggregation semantics.\n- Any `3702f54` metrics derived from trial-averaged `forward_vel_profile` traces before alignment, especially within-cell velocity-profile RMSE / variance summaries and downstream summary-metric displays/specs, should be audited before interpretation.\n- `scripts/analyse_lit_replication_6cell.py` has the same absolute-time `v_fwd.mean(axis=1)` / mean-go-vline pattern for `f47abb1` forward velocity profiles.\n- `results/f47abb1/figures/forward_velocity_profiles/figure.html` and related velocity-profile specs/metrics are therefore likely affected in the same way.\n\nKnown not affected by this specific bug:\n\n- `/tmp/flavor_ab_review/plots/forward_velocity_canonical_15cm.html`: deterministic Riccati 15 cm reach, no randomized go cue / trial alignment issue.\n- `/tmp/flavor_ab_review/plots/forward_velocity_0p5m.html`: the scratch generator documents and implements a per-trial go-cue alignment correction before averaging.\n- `/tmp/flavor_ab_review/plots/forward_velocity_baseline_matrix.html`: the scratch baseline-matrix generator inspected in this discussion also performs per-trial go-cue window extraction before averaging.\n\n## Correct semantics\nThe intended operation is not interpolation or resampling. For each trial, allocate a relative-time array with NaN padding, copy raw samples so `relative_index = raw_index - go_idx[trial]`, and then aggregate with NaN-aware reductions. The go cue should be at `t=0` for every trial.\n\nTwo different uncertainty bands should be named distinctly:\n\n- Replicate-mean band: average trials within each replicate after alignment, then compute SD across replicate means.\n- Trial-level band: treat every replicate-trial aligned trace as a sample, then compute SD across all replicate-trials.\n\nThe old figures mostly used replicate-mean variance after absolute-time trial averaging. They should not be used as evidence about trial-level early-vs-late go-cue variability.\n\n## What to fix / audit\n- Patch the affected analysis scripts to align each trial to its own go cue before velocity-profile plotting or RMSE-profile calculations when the metric is intended to be go-aligned.\n- Regenerate affected HTML figures and figure specs with explicit transform names such as `align_trials_to_go_by_integer_index_nan_padding` and `nanmean_over_trials`.\n- Recompute any velocity-profile RMSE / replicate-variance metrics whose interpretation assumed go alignment.\n- Preserve scalar metrics that already use go masks/indexing only if their implementations are independently verified; peak post-go velocity and time-to-peak appeared to use `go_idx` directly, but should still be audited.\n- Add a small regression test or fixture for variable go-cue indices verifying that a synthetic post-go pulse aligns to `t=0` before trial averaging.\n\n## Related issues / artifacts\n- `bf71d86`: follow-up analysis for go-cue timing stratification and anticipation onset.\n- `5acdaae`: reduce / eliminate pre-go-cue anticipation.\n- `3702f54`: pre-go motor-mask follow-up matrix.\n- `f47abb1`: lit-replication 6-cell matrix.\n- Temporary Codex diagnostic artifacts: `/tmp/rlrmp_go_alignment_diagnostics/3702f54_forward_velocity_trial_variance_subplots_2_7.html` and matching `_stats.json`.\n\n---\nCo-Authored-By: Codex (GPT-5) \u003ccodex@openai.com\u003e","files":null}]}